1
00:00:01,585 --> 00:00:03,301
[theme music plays]

2
00:01:22,499 --> 00:01:28,422
OVERCAST

3
00:01:36,221 --> 00:01:38,432
[Light] Regardless of how she came
to the conclusion,

4
00:01:38,515 --> 00:01:40,934
the fact remains
this woman knows the truth.

5
00:01:41,602 --> 00:01:43,687
If she gives this information
to the police,

6
00:01:43,895 --> 00:01:47,274
it won't take them very long
to figure out that Kira is actually me.

7
00:01:48,525 --> 00:01:50,569
I have no choice but to eliminate her.

8
00:01:51,403 --> 00:01:52,529
[Naomi] Something wrong?

9
00:01:54,323 --> 00:01:55,824
[Light] Oh, it's nothing.

10
00:01:57,284 --> 00:02:00,537
But the more I think about it,
the more your theory makes sense to me.

11
00:02:00,996 --> 00:02:02,331
We can't waste any time.

12
00:02:02,456 --> 00:02:04,333
We need to start investigating it
right away.

13
00:02:04,583 --> 00:02:06,376
What? Really? Do you mean that?

14
00:02:06,543 --> 00:02:07,544
Yes.

15
00:02:07,878 --> 00:02:09,880
So, have you told anyone else about this?

16
00:02:10,088 --> 00:02:12,215
No, you're the first person I've told.

17
00:02:13,050 --> 00:02:14,301
[Ryuk chuckles]

18
00:02:14,426 --> 00:02:17,179
You're lucky.
But how will you get rid of her?

19
00:02:17,387 --> 00:02:19,222
It's not like you can do it here.

20
00:02:19,681 --> 00:02:22,643
[Light] Well, you have a gift
for stating the obvious, Ryuk.

21
00:02:23,894 --> 00:02:25,771
Oh, aren't you bold?

22
00:02:26,146 --> 00:02:27,147
Let's get started.

23
00:02:27,230 --> 00:02:30,442
Could you please tell me the date and time
of the bus-jacking incident?

24
00:02:30,692 --> 00:02:33,487
It was December 20th,
in front of Asagao Hill.

25
00:02:33,820 --> 00:02:36,782
At 11:02 a.m., bound for Space Land.

26
00:02:37,824 --> 00:02:43,330
December 20th, and they were
on their way to Space Land.

27
00:02:43,622 --> 00:02:44,623
[Naomi] Yes.

28
00:02:44,706 --> 00:02:46,541
SHOKO MAKI
SUICIDE JANUARY 1, 2007

29
00:02:46,625 --> 00:02:49,336
Commits suicide in such a way
that nobody will be inconvenienced,

30
00:02:49,419 --> 00:02:51,254
and her body will not be discovered.

31
00:02:51,338 --> 00:02:53,507
Dies by implementing this plan
within 48 hours.

32
00:02:54,341 --> 00:02:56,468
[Light] This way,
no one will find her body.

33
00:02:56,802 --> 00:02:58,512
And even if they do, they'll just assume

34
00:02:58,637 --> 00:03:01,682
that the death of her fiancé
drove her to commit suicide.

35
00:03:02,099 --> 00:03:03,975
[Ryuk chuckling]

36
00:03:04,476 --> 00:03:05,936
[Light] What's so funny, Ryuk?

37
00:03:06,019 --> 00:03:11,191
[Ryuk laughs maniacally]

38
00:03:12,609 --> 00:03:15,153
[L] I apologize for questioning
all of you like that,

39
00:03:15,278 --> 00:03:16,947
but I'm afraid I had no other choice.

40
00:03:17,239 --> 00:03:19,366
I've determined that Kira is not among us.

41
00:03:19,825 --> 00:03:20,951
[all sighing in relief]

42
00:03:21,702 --> 00:03:24,830
Ryuzaki, how can you be certain
that we're all innocent?

43
00:03:25,330 --> 00:03:28,583
Well, to be honest, from the beginning,
I set a number of traps

44
00:03:28,709 --> 00:03:30,544
that would reveal if any of you was Kira.

45
00:03:31,253 --> 00:03:34,798
But after speaking with you one on one,
I don't feel the need.

46
00:03:35,298 --> 00:03:36,174
[all sighing]

47
00:03:36,466 --> 00:03:38,135
[phone ringing]

48
00:03:38,802 --> 00:03:39,803
Excuse me.

49
00:03:42,931 --> 00:03:45,767
Unbelievable. He tells us
to turn off our cellphones...

50
00:03:46,435 --> 00:03:47,477
Understood.

51
00:03:47,561 --> 00:03:49,312
I'm just about finished here anyway.

52
00:03:49,396 --> 00:03:51,273
You've got the key, so let yourself in.

53
00:03:53,442 --> 00:03:54,568
Watari is on his way.

54
00:03:54,901 --> 00:03:55,902
[all gasping]

55
00:03:56,653 --> 00:03:57,779
So, that's everything.

56
00:03:58,029 --> 00:03:59,906
I'd like to report this incident
to my father.

57
00:03:59,990 --> 00:04:01,408
If it's okay with you, that is.

58
00:04:01,908 --> 00:04:05,704
Well, if it's all the same,
I think I'd like to report it myself.

59
00:04:05,829 --> 00:04:07,164
And after talking to you,

60
00:04:07,247 --> 00:04:09,833
I've decided that it would be best
to do it as soon as possible.

61
00:04:12,544 --> 00:04:14,087
[Light] Uh, that makes sense.

62
00:04:17,090 --> 00:04:19,760
Just ten seconds until 1:15…

63
00:04:20,343 --> 00:04:23,805
I have to admit,
I'd really love to see how she dies.

64
00:04:24,264 --> 00:04:26,433
But I can't be caught
following her around.

65
00:04:28,310 --> 00:04:31,688
Go on, hurry to your death!

66
00:04:33,565 --> 00:04:34,983
[ticking]

67
00:04:41,782 --> 00:04:45,243
[clock ticking]

68
00:04:45,452 --> 00:04:48,121
[Naomi] Kira will definitely be caught.
Don't you think?

69
00:04:48,330 --> 00:04:49,456
Huh?

70
00:04:50,540 --> 00:04:53,752
[ticking]

71
00:04:54,753 --> 00:04:57,422
What's going on?
It should have happened already.

72
00:05:01,051 --> 00:05:04,638
This doesn't make sense.
I don't understand why she's not leaving.

73
00:05:05,013 --> 00:05:05,889
SUICIDE

74
00:05:05,972 --> 00:05:08,433
I've had no problems making people
kill themselves in the past.

75
00:05:08,517 --> 00:05:10,519
All I had to do is
write the word "suicide."

76
00:05:10,977 --> 00:05:12,938
The criminals I tested it on
all hung themselves

77
00:05:13,021 --> 00:05:15,023
exactly when I specified.

78
00:05:15,440 --> 00:05:18,068
My experiments indicate
that in a situation like this,

79
00:05:18,193 --> 00:05:20,654
I should be able to control
a person's actions.

80
00:05:20,987 --> 00:05:22,030
So, what's wrong?

81
00:05:22,489 --> 00:05:27,035
[Ryuk laughing]

82
00:05:27,577 --> 00:05:28,745
[Light] Ryuk…

83
00:05:29,663 --> 00:05:32,791
He laughed just like that
when I was writing in the Death Note.

84
00:05:33,375 --> 00:05:34,668
[Light] And that's not all.

85
00:05:35,126 --> 00:05:38,255
I remember thinking it was bizarre
how he laughed when I asked for her name.

86
00:05:38,380 --> 00:05:41,716
In fact, he's reacted the same way
every time her name comes up.

87
00:05:42,092 --> 00:05:43,802
An alias!

88
00:05:48,181 --> 00:05:49,558
[all gasping]

89
00:05:53,311 --> 00:05:55,355
Gentlemen,
it's an honor to meet all of you.

90
00:05:56,690 --> 00:05:58,441
This person is Watari?

91
00:05:58,859 --> 00:06:00,610
Hm. What about your usual outfit?

92
00:06:01,486 --> 00:06:05,031
If I dressed like that, I'd be announcing
to the world that I am Watari.

93
00:06:05,282 --> 00:06:07,742
That's all it takes to give away
the location of our headquarters

94
00:06:07,826 --> 00:06:08,702
and Ryuzaki.

95
00:06:09,119 --> 00:06:10,412
Oh, I see.

96
00:06:10,912 --> 00:06:13,874
Ordinarily, I would never show my face
to any of you.

97
00:06:13,957 --> 00:06:17,043
The fact that I'm here is proof
that you've won Ryuzaki's trust.

98
00:06:17,377 --> 00:06:19,796
Now that you mention it,
I do feel honored.

99
00:06:20,088 --> 00:06:22,257
[nervous laughter]

100
00:06:22,591 --> 00:06:25,093
Well then, I've brought those items
you requested.

101
00:06:25,176 --> 00:06:26,094
It's all here.

102
00:06:26,386 --> 00:06:28,513
Could you please pass them out
to everyone?

103
00:06:28,722 --> 00:06:29,806
[Watari] Yes.

104
00:06:32,893 --> 00:06:35,312
[Watari] Gentlemen,
these are your new police IDs.

105
00:06:35,395 --> 00:06:37,147
-[all] Huh?
-But what for?

106
00:06:39,691 --> 00:06:41,693
[Light] She used an alias,
that has to be it!

107
00:06:41,943 --> 00:06:43,361
But Ryuk knew all along.

108
00:06:43,486 --> 00:06:45,530
He could see her real name with his eyes.

109
00:06:45,655 --> 00:06:48,116
That's why he wouldn't stop laughing.
I should've known.

110
00:06:48,450 --> 00:06:50,702
She's been overly cautious
from the beginning.

111
00:06:52,746 --> 00:06:54,247
I see. It makes a lot of sense.

112
00:06:54,372 --> 00:06:57,375
She believes that Raye died
because he showed his ID to Kira.

113
00:06:57,959 --> 00:07:00,837
So, of course she'd be careful
not to reveal her own identity.

114
00:07:02,380 --> 00:07:03,882
Oh, this isn't good.

115
00:07:04,382 --> 00:07:06,718
It's gonna be almost impossible
to ask for her real name

116
00:07:06,801 --> 00:07:08,929
knowing she gave me an alias
the first time.

117
00:07:09,262 --> 00:07:11,431
If I'm too persistent,
she'll get suspicious.

118
00:07:11,973 --> 00:07:13,099
What am I saying?

119
00:07:13,183 --> 00:07:16,019
It looks suspicious that I even knew
she was using an alias.

120
00:07:17,604 --> 00:07:20,357
-I should probably be getting back soon.
-Hmm?

121
00:07:20,774 --> 00:07:23,193
Someone from the Task Force
might be back there by now.

122
00:07:23,735 --> 00:07:25,946
[Light] Oh, yeah, you could be right.

123
00:07:26,446 --> 00:07:28,990
Let's cross our fingers
and hope someone's there.

124
00:07:29,074 --> 00:07:29,991
Yeah.

125
00:07:33,495 --> 00:07:35,956
Damn it! I'm running out of options here.

126
00:07:41,044 --> 00:07:43,171
I have to stop this before it's too late.

127
00:07:44,923 --> 00:07:47,801
Oh, no. What if my father calls back now?

128
00:07:48,093 --> 00:07:50,804
I already promised her
that I'd let her talk to him if he did.

129
00:07:51,179 --> 00:07:53,932
If this phone rings, it's all over for me.
What am I gonna do?

130
00:07:57,268 --> 00:08:00,063
This is crazy. All I have to do
is turn my cellphone off.

131
00:08:00,730 --> 00:08:02,440
-[phone beeps]
-[Light] Problem solved.

132
00:08:02,774 --> 00:08:04,150
Now, calm down.

133
00:08:04,401 --> 00:08:07,195
You know what needs to be done.
Just find out her real name.

134
00:08:07,612 --> 00:08:09,072
Her purse, her pockets...

135
00:08:09,155 --> 00:08:10,824
She's got to have a driver's license

136
00:08:10,949 --> 00:08:13,493
or some sort of personal identification
on her somewhere.

137
00:08:13,618 --> 00:08:14,953
She's a woman, after all.

138
00:08:15,328 --> 00:08:17,580
I suppose if I had to, I could use force.

139
00:08:18,498 --> 00:08:21,751
No, no, the last thing I want to do
is make a scene in public.

140
00:08:22,293 --> 00:08:24,170
I've got to get her somewhere isolated.

141
00:08:24,587 --> 00:08:27,674
But where?
And what explanation could I give her?

142
00:08:28,091 --> 00:08:31,886
It would never work. She's too careful.
I need a better approach.

143
00:08:33,013 --> 00:08:34,305
I can do this.

144
00:08:34,472 --> 00:08:37,183
I'm going to convince her
to give me her real name.

145
00:08:37,267 --> 00:08:39,102
[Ryuk laughs]

146
00:08:39,519 --> 00:08:43,148
Hey, Light, you know,
that deal I mentioned is still open.

147
00:08:43,481 --> 00:08:45,900
It's just like putting on contact lenses.

148
00:08:46,192 --> 00:08:47,485
Completely painless.

149
00:08:47,986 --> 00:08:50,238
Would I be willing to give up half my life

150
00:08:50,488 --> 00:08:52,490
just so I can learn
this woman's real name?

151
00:08:53,783 --> 00:08:55,410
No, I wouldn't.

152
00:08:55,535 --> 00:08:57,620
In fact, it's not even worth considering.

153
00:08:57,787 --> 00:09:00,665
Now quit wasting my time.
Just shut your mouth, Shinigami.

154
00:09:01,249 --> 00:09:03,084
-Excuse me.
-Yes?

155
00:09:03,501 --> 00:09:06,171
Uh, do you still have business
at the police station then?

156
00:09:06,296 --> 00:09:08,923
I'd like to go there by myself,
if you don't mind.

157
00:09:11,176 --> 00:09:12,510
Yeah, no problem.

158
00:09:13,303 --> 00:09:15,180
[Soichiro] Our names and ranks are false.

159
00:09:15,979 --> 00:09:17,640
[Matsuda] Why did you give us fake IDs?

160
00:09:18,224 --> 00:09:21,352
As you know, Kira requires
a name and a face to kill.

161
00:09:21,478 --> 00:09:22,687
[L slurps, gulps]

162
00:09:22,771 --> 00:09:24,981
We will confront him
with that premise in mind.

163
00:09:25,106 --> 00:09:26,691
And I think it should be obvious why.

164
00:09:27,025 --> 00:09:30,195
Yes, but of all people,
the police shouldn't use fake IDs.

165
00:09:30,528 --> 00:09:34,240
Enough. What choice do we really have,
given the capabilities of our enemy?

166
00:09:34,407 --> 00:09:35,992
As long as you're working on this case,

167
00:09:36,076 --> 00:09:38,369
I think we're going to need
all the protection one can get.

168
00:09:38,828 --> 00:09:40,371
It would be foolish not to use them.

169
00:09:40,580 --> 00:09:43,333
-Yeah. You've got a good point.
-Uh-huh.

170
00:09:43,708 --> 00:09:45,627
Remember, any time you're in a situation

171
00:09:45,710 --> 00:09:47,754
where you have to give out your name
to a stranger,

172
00:09:47,837 --> 00:09:50,256
make sure to use the name
from your fake ID. Understood?

173
00:09:50,423 --> 00:09:51,883
-Hmm.
-Right.

174
00:09:51,966 --> 00:09:55,053
And be careful not to take them out while
in the presence of other police officers.

175
00:09:55,136 --> 00:09:56,638
I'm sure I don't need to tell you.

176
00:09:57,180 --> 00:09:58,890
That could cause problems for us.

177
00:09:59,265 --> 00:10:01,142
-I understand.
-[men grunting in approval]

178
00:10:01,309 --> 00:10:02,644
[Watari] Very well, then.

179
00:10:03,603 --> 00:10:06,314
I'd like to request
that you wear these at all times.

180
00:10:06,606 --> 00:10:07,774
Uh, belts?

181
00:10:08,817 --> 00:10:11,402
Each one has a transmitter
hidden in the buckle.

182
00:10:11,611 --> 00:10:14,405
This will allow Ryuzaki
to monitor your whereabouts.

183
00:10:14,948 --> 00:10:17,617
And when you press the buckle
twice like this...

184
00:10:17,867 --> 00:10:18,827
[phone ringing]

185
00:10:18,993 --> 00:10:21,788
...my cellphone will ring,
displaying your name.

186
00:10:22,163 --> 00:10:25,667
And I'll call you back immediately,
but you won't see my number displayed.

187
00:10:26,084 --> 00:10:29,420
In the morning, all of you will go
to the police station as usual.

188
00:10:29,671 --> 00:10:31,506
Then, later on in the day,

189
00:10:31,631 --> 00:10:35,760
we'll use this method to confirm the name
of Ryuzaki's hotel and his room number.

190
00:10:35,844 --> 00:10:38,388
Please use this for emergencies as well.

191
00:10:38,513 --> 00:10:40,306
No way! This is totally cool.

192
00:10:40,390 --> 00:10:42,433
I feel like some kind of secret agent
going after Kira!

193
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:43,685
Quiet, Matsuda!

194
00:10:43,810 --> 00:10:45,895
This is not the time to be fooling around.

195
00:10:45,979 --> 00:10:48,356
-Knock it off!
-Yes, sir.

196
00:10:49,149 --> 00:10:51,484
Thank you so much
for everything you've done, Light.

197
00:10:51,734 --> 00:10:55,196
After talking to you, I feel
much more confident about my theory.

198
00:10:55,738 --> 00:10:56,948
Not at all.

199
00:11:03,746 --> 00:11:06,457
Considering that Ryuk mentioned
that eye deal again,

200
00:11:06,708 --> 00:11:09,335
there's no doubt in my mind
that she used an alias.

201
00:11:10,378 --> 00:11:12,422
At this rate, once she goes to the police

202
00:11:12,505 --> 00:11:14,716
with her theory about Kira
being on that bus,

203
00:11:15,008 --> 00:11:17,510
and they look at all the people
Raye Penber was investigating,

204
00:11:17,802 --> 00:11:19,929
it won't take them long to zero in on me.

205
00:11:20,305 --> 00:11:21,681
[Ryuk chuckles]

206
00:11:21,890 --> 00:11:24,767
Hey, she's leaving. So now what?

207
00:11:26,269 --> 00:11:27,395
I've got about five minutes

208
00:11:27,478 --> 00:11:29,355
before that woman
gets to police headquarters.

209
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:30,440
Think!

210
00:11:30,648 --> 00:11:33,776
I need her real name,
and I don't have much time to spare.

211
00:11:55,381 --> 00:11:57,425
[Light] If this woman makes it
to the police station

212
00:11:57,508 --> 00:11:59,761
and someone from the Task Force
has returned by then,

213
00:11:59,969 --> 00:12:01,304
it'll all be over for me.

214
00:12:02,055 --> 00:12:05,516
I've got to find out her real name
and eliminate her quickly.

215
00:12:06,059 --> 00:12:08,686
Only three minutes left
until she reaches the station.

216
00:12:10,772 --> 00:12:11,940
All right.

217
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:14,108
Oh? Whatcha doing?

218
00:12:14,692 --> 00:12:16,444
-Excuse me.
-Yes?

219
00:12:17,028 --> 00:12:19,697
There's something
that I should probably tell you.

220
00:12:19,989 --> 00:12:20,865
Okay.

221
00:12:21,950 --> 00:12:23,868
The thing is, it'll be impossible for you

222
00:12:23,993 --> 00:12:26,246
to contact anyone
from the Task Force directly.

223
00:12:26,412 --> 00:12:27,372
Huh?

224
00:12:28,081 --> 00:12:30,250
[Light] That's right.
Keep the conversation going.

225
00:12:30,375 --> 00:12:33,503
I just need to find something
that she can latch onto and I've got her.

226
00:12:33,586 --> 00:12:35,922
Once she's comfortable,
then I can get her real name.

227
00:12:36,089 --> 00:12:37,215
I can do this.

228
00:12:37,423 --> 00:12:39,467
I can't contact anyone? But why not?

229
00:12:39,676 --> 00:12:42,804
Didn't you think it odd that there
was no one at Task Force headquarters?

230
00:12:42,971 --> 00:12:44,180
Uh, yeah.

231
00:12:44,305 --> 00:12:46,349
I did find it a bit strange,
but I didn't...

232
00:12:46,474 --> 00:12:47,517
Let me explain.

233
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:50,478
The Task Force has been organized
so that its members can't be identified

234
00:12:50,561 --> 00:12:52,939
if nobody on the outside knows
who's in charge.

235
00:12:53,022 --> 00:12:53,940
Hmm.

236
00:12:54,274 --> 00:12:56,401
If the members' names
were ever made public

237
00:12:56,526 --> 00:12:58,778
or the structure of the Task Force
was revealed,

238
00:12:58,861 --> 00:13:00,363
we'd likely see another tragedy

239
00:13:00,446 --> 00:13:03,074
along the lines of the one
that claimed your fiancé's life.

240
00:13:08,371 --> 00:13:09,414
I see.

241
00:13:10,081 --> 00:13:11,749
[Light] That's why you were told earlier

242
00:13:11,874 --> 00:13:13,835
that no one was
at Task Force headquarters.

243
00:13:14,669 --> 00:13:15,962
What I'm trying to say is,

244
00:13:16,045 --> 00:13:18,715
you'll never be able to talk to someone
directly from the Task Force

245
00:13:18,798 --> 00:13:20,508
because the police simply won't allow it.

246
00:13:23,052 --> 00:13:24,220
[Ryuk chuckles]

247
00:13:24,470 --> 00:13:26,597
That's pretty clever. I'm impressed.

248
00:13:27,140 --> 00:13:30,059
If this is supposed to be a secret,
then how do you know so much?

249
00:13:31,436 --> 00:13:33,479
Guess I spoke too soon. She's sharp.

250
00:13:36,858 --> 00:13:39,193
Very well. You leave me no choice.

251
00:13:40,361 --> 00:13:42,780
It's because I'm actually a member
of the Task Force.

252
00:13:42,864 --> 00:13:43,740
[Ryuk] Huh?

253
00:13:44,240 --> 00:13:46,409
I'm sorry, you're telling me
that you're an agent?

254
00:13:46,826 --> 00:13:49,662
Yes. L is currently in charge
of the Task Force,

255
00:13:49,746 --> 00:13:51,331
and he's leading our investigation.

256
00:13:51,539 --> 00:13:54,292
Yes. To be honest,
I already suspected that.

257
00:13:54,584 --> 00:13:57,962
He was concerned that the Task Force
had become too small.

258
00:13:58,671 --> 00:14:01,841
Many detectives had quit,
fearing for their lives. And so...

259
00:14:02,133 --> 00:14:04,093
despite the fact
that I'm a high school student,

260
00:14:04,469 --> 00:14:06,971
he brought me on board
to help out with the investigation.

261
00:14:07,055 --> 00:14:09,557
After all, I've helped them solve cases
in the past.

262
00:14:09,849 --> 00:14:11,601
So, L trusts you then?

263
00:14:12,143 --> 00:14:15,104
I can go to Task Force headquarters
whenever it suits me

264
00:14:15,229 --> 00:14:17,982
and I'm allowed to investigate freely
as I see fit.

265
00:14:18,232 --> 00:14:22,111
You see, these days, the Task Force
is made up of a chosen few,

266
00:14:22,236 --> 00:14:25,281
an elite group of people
handpicked for the job by L.

267
00:14:25,573 --> 00:14:29,619
All are highly skilled, well respected,
and above all, trustworthy.

268
00:14:30,119 --> 00:14:31,204
[gasps]

269
00:14:32,705 --> 00:14:37,335
[Ryuk laughs]

270
00:14:41,672 --> 00:14:43,966
Thanks for explaining.
But just to be safe,

271
00:14:44,092 --> 00:14:46,511
I'd like to try and visit
the Task Force headquarters again.

272
00:14:46,719 --> 00:14:48,221
-Huh?
-Goodbye.

273
00:14:51,265 --> 00:14:52,892
Please, wait a second!

274
00:14:53,559 --> 00:14:56,687
It's like I just told you.
They won't let you talk to anyone.

275
00:14:57,146 --> 00:15:00,274
[Naomi] I know, but I was hoping
I could speak with L directly.

276
00:15:04,904 --> 00:15:08,116
Oh, and come to think of it,
who's at the police station right now?

277
00:15:08,366 --> 00:15:10,034
Actually, no one's there at the moment.

278
00:15:10,243 --> 00:15:11,744
That's not good news.

279
00:15:11,869 --> 00:15:15,123
We need someone there at all times.
Work in shifts if you have to.

280
00:15:15,331 --> 00:15:18,543
I understand. Aizawa,
I'll put you in charge of that for today.

281
00:15:18,793 --> 00:15:21,754
Yes, sir. I'm on my way.
Won't take me long.

282
00:15:22,130 --> 00:15:24,132
Ms. Maki, please wait a second.

283
00:15:24,382 --> 00:15:27,635
It's literally impossible to meet L.
This is pointless.

284
00:15:32,432 --> 00:15:33,599
You may be right.

285
00:15:33,683 --> 00:15:35,852
But I think there's a chance
that he'll meet with me.

286
00:15:36,811 --> 00:15:38,813
[Naomi] Although the only contact
I've had with him

287
00:15:38,896 --> 00:15:40,815
was following orders through a computer.

288
00:15:40,982 --> 00:15:42,525
He might remember who I am.

289
00:15:42,775 --> 00:15:46,112
You see, I worked under him
in a case in the US about two years ago.

290
00:15:47,155 --> 00:15:48,990
Are you serious? You worked under L?

291
00:15:49,740 --> 00:15:51,701
Yes, I didn't tell you this, but...

292
00:15:51,909 --> 00:15:54,620
up until three months ago,
I worked as an FBI agent.

293
00:15:56,289 --> 00:15:58,875
This is it. Finally something I can use.

294
00:16:00,084 --> 00:16:01,461
Guess I shouldn't be surprised.

295
00:16:01,586 --> 00:16:03,129
In fact, I noticed early on

296
00:16:03,212 --> 00:16:06,299
that your investigative skills
were far beyond those of an amateur.

297
00:16:06,674 --> 00:16:07,717
You're very cautious

298
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:10,595
and you seem to have a gift
for getting to the heart of the matter.

299
00:16:10,678 --> 00:16:12,638
If I could, I'd like to learn from you.

300
00:16:12,722 --> 00:16:14,307
[Ryuk laughs]

301
00:16:14,390 --> 00:16:16,767
One lie after another.
You make it look easy.

302
00:16:17,560 --> 00:16:20,605
From the beginning, I knew I had
to do things outside the regular channels

303
00:16:20,688 --> 00:16:21,856
because from my perspective,

304
00:16:21,939 --> 00:16:24,775
both the police and the members
of the Task Force were suspects.

305
00:16:25,693 --> 00:16:27,778
But I'm certain that I can trust L.

306
00:16:29,530 --> 00:16:31,032
Maybe it's unrealistic,

307
00:16:31,449 --> 00:16:34,535
but I think that if I go to headquarters
and I give them my name,

308
00:16:34,744 --> 00:16:37,622
there's a chance that they'll let me
speak with him directly.

309
00:16:37,914 --> 00:16:39,040
I see…

310
00:16:39,665 --> 00:16:43,252
But if the only person you could trust
with this info was L, then why me?

311
00:16:44,420 --> 00:16:46,714
I suppose I was upset
that they wouldn't allow me

312
00:16:46,839 --> 00:16:48,382
to see anyone from the Task Force.

313
00:16:48,466 --> 00:16:49,634
And then you came along,

314
00:16:49,717 --> 00:16:52,053
claiming to be the son
of the lead detective and...

315
00:16:52,345 --> 00:16:54,472
No, that's not it.

316
00:16:56,182 --> 00:16:57,642
[Naomi] I'll be honest with you.

317
00:16:58,142 --> 00:17:00,394
It's because you remind me of L.

318
00:17:01,687 --> 00:17:04,148
There's something about you
that's just like him.

319
00:17:05,566 --> 00:17:06,734
Hmm.

320
00:17:13,491 --> 00:17:15,826
-Will you investigate this case with me?
-Huh?

321
00:17:16,661 --> 00:17:19,288
I want you to come work with us
as part of the Task Force.

322
00:17:19,372 --> 00:17:20,373
We could use your help.

323
00:17:21,415 --> 00:17:23,876
[Light] As I'm sure you know,
not just anyone can do it.

324
00:17:24,335 --> 00:17:27,547
Please, I know this is sudden
but the team needs people like you.

325
00:17:27,838 --> 00:17:28,881
I'm serious.

326
00:17:28,965 --> 00:17:31,884
You could be doing so much more
than gathering information on your own.

327
00:17:31,968 --> 00:17:34,387
You have all the experience
as an FBI agent.

328
00:17:34,470 --> 00:17:36,389
You're more talented
than most of the detectives

329
00:17:36,514 --> 00:17:37,765
currently on the Task Force.

330
00:17:37,848 --> 00:17:40,101
And L obviously trusted you in the past.

331
00:17:40,434 --> 00:17:42,436
It wouldn't be that difficult
for you to join.

332
00:17:42,520 --> 00:17:44,480
All you'd need
is some valid identification,

333
00:17:44,564 --> 00:17:46,983
a recommendation
from a current Task Force member,

334
00:17:47,149 --> 00:17:49,360
and, of course,
you'd need to get L's permission.

335
00:17:49,819 --> 00:17:51,779
You want me to join the Task Force?

336
00:17:52,405 --> 00:17:55,616
I can't help but think
that it must be fate that I met you today.

337
00:17:55,908 --> 00:17:58,077
I'd like to be the one to recommend you.

338
00:18:02,248 --> 00:18:03,874
Oh, I'm sorry about that.

339
00:18:04,208 --> 00:18:07,044
-I guess I got a little bit too excited.
-It's okay.

340
00:18:07,253 --> 00:18:10,298
I mean, even if you acted
as a consultant on this investigation,

341
00:18:10,381 --> 00:18:11,632
it would be a great help.

342
00:18:11,757 --> 00:18:14,176
I'm sure you have personal obligations
to attend to.

343
00:18:14,260 --> 00:18:16,512
Not to mention the fact
that you live in the United States.

344
00:18:17,263 --> 00:18:19,265
It's true. Before all this happened,

345
00:18:19,348 --> 00:18:22,310
I thought I'd continue living in America
with my fiancé.

346
00:18:22,476 --> 00:18:24,604
We'd planned on getting married
in the spring.

347
00:18:25,187 --> 00:18:27,982
But now he's gone,
so I'm not sure what to do anymore.

348
00:18:28,357 --> 00:18:31,986
All right. I've come this far.
All she needs is a little encouragement.

349
00:18:32,403 --> 00:18:35,323
But you're young and beautiful,
and you've got your life ahead of you.

350
00:18:35,406 --> 00:18:37,074
Why put it all in danger for this?

351
00:18:37,408 --> 00:18:40,494
No! Now that Raye's gone,
I've got nothing to lose anymore.

352
00:18:40,661 --> 00:18:41,954
I want to catch Kira!

353
00:18:42,079 --> 00:18:44,415
I don't care about anything else.
It's all I want to do.

354
00:18:44,540 --> 00:18:46,709
Please let me investigate this case
with you.

355
00:18:46,834 --> 00:18:47,835
Huh?

356
00:18:48,336 --> 00:18:55,301
[Ryuk laughs maniacally]

357
00:18:55,760 --> 00:18:57,011
Yes, of course.

358
00:18:57,553 --> 00:19:01,182
I just need to see some form
of identification before we proceed.

359
00:19:01,515 --> 00:19:03,934
-Oh, um...
-Yes?

360
00:19:04,435 --> 00:19:06,687
You see, the name
I gave you earlier, well...

361
00:19:06,979 --> 00:19:09,023
it wasn't actually my real name.

362
00:19:09,565 --> 00:19:10,608
I'm so sorry.

363
00:19:12,777 --> 00:19:14,278
Don't worry, it's all right.

364
00:19:14,403 --> 00:19:17,740
To be honest, I'm impressed
by how incredibly thorough you've been.

365
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:20,117
You've stayed one step ahead of me.

366
00:19:20,284 --> 00:19:22,953
But I suppose that's just further proof
of your capabilities.

367
00:19:23,287 --> 00:19:25,998
So will a Japanese driver's license
do the trick then?

368
00:19:26,165 --> 00:19:27,249
Sure.

369
00:19:46,310 --> 00:19:47,812
[Light] I made it in time.

370
00:19:48,020 --> 00:19:49,855
NAOMI MISORA
DATE OF BIRTH: 2/11/1979

371
00:19:50,022 --> 00:19:51,607
NAOMI MISORA
SUICIDE 1/1/2007

372
00:20:03,911 --> 00:20:07,915
Uh, so, if you don't mind my asking,
why do you keep checking your watch?

373
00:20:08,666 --> 00:20:10,459
Oh, well...

374
00:20:11,836 --> 00:20:13,254
I guess it's because…

375
00:20:16,298 --> 00:20:17,508
Because I'm Kira.

376
00:20:18,008 --> 00:20:19,176
[gasps]

377
00:20:21,429 --> 00:20:22,638
[ticking]

378
00:20:48,581 --> 00:20:49,832
What's the matter?

379
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:52,835
[Naomi] There's something I have to do.

380
00:20:54,086 --> 00:20:55,087
Hmm.

381
00:20:56,922 --> 00:20:59,467
My father's cellphone
might be available now.

382
00:20:59,925 --> 00:21:01,802
Do you wanna see
if you can talk to him?

383
00:21:03,012 --> 00:21:05,765
[Naomi] No, thank you.
I have nothing to say to him.

384
00:21:07,475 --> 00:21:10,269
Then, goodbye, Naomi Misora.

385
00:21:30,456 --> 00:21:36,378
TO BE CONTINUED

386
00:21:38,464 --> 00:21:41,759
[theme music plays]
